        "subject": "LU-19886 utils: fix buffer overflow in lshowmount nidlist",
        "message": "LU-19886 utils: fix buffer overflow in lshowmount nidlist\n\nnl_strxcat() passes max_len (total buffer size) as the size\nargument to the first snprintf() call, but the write position\nis s + strlen(s), so the available space is only\nmax_len - strlen(s). With FORTIFY_SOURCE=3 (default on el10),\nglibc detects that the size argument exceeds the remaining\nobject size and aborts with \"buffer overflow detected\".\n\nSimilarly, nl_xstring() passes len (total buffer size) as the\ncount argument to strncat(), which should be the maximum number\nof characters to append, not the total buffer size. The correct\nvalue is len - strlen(s) - 1 (remaining space minus null\nterminator).\n\nFix all four instances to use the remaining buffer space rather\nthan the total allocation size.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial testlist=conf-sanity env=ONLY=100\nChange-Id: I6f43ea3b18330ea074f9edaf97cda51cd00ab508\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/c/fs/lustre-release/+/64110\nTested-by: Maloo <maloo@whamcloud.com>\nTested-by: jenkins <devops@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <adilger@thelustrecollective.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <green@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev <bzzz@whamcloud.com>\nReviewed-by: James Simmons <jsimmons@infradead.org>\n"
      },
